    <description><![CDATA[ocicl is a modern package manager for Common Lisp that uses OCI (Open Container Initiative) registries for distribution.

## Features

- Fast, reliable package installation from OCI registries
- Project-local and global package management
- Dependency resolution and version pinning
- Built-in linter for Common Lisp code
- SBOM (Software Bill of Materials) generation
- License collection and management
- Project templates for quick starts

## Requirements

ocicl requires SBCL (Steel Bank Common Lisp) to be installed:
- Install with: `choco install sbcl`

## Usage

After installation, run `ocicl` from the command line:

```
ocicl help               # Show all commands
ocicl install PKG        # Install a package
ocicl install            # Install all packages from ocicl.csv
ocicl list PKG           # List available versions
ocicl latest PKG         # Update to latest version
ocicl remove PKG         # Remove a package
ocicl new NAME TEMPLATE  # Create new project from template
ocicl lint FILE          # Lint Common Lisp code
```

## Quick Start

```
mkdir my-project && cd my-project
ocicl install alexandria cl-ppcre
```

Then in your Lisp:
```lisp
(asdf:load-system :alexandria)
```
]]></description>
